casebody.data:
TYRRELL v. CROUSE, WARDEN. No. 59,

Mise.

Decided October 14, 1968. Robert C. Londerholm, Attorney General of Kansas, and J. Richard Foth and Jon K. Sargent, Assistant Attorneys General, for respondent. Per Curiam.

The motion for leave to proceed in forma pauperis and the petition for a writ of certiorari are granted. In accordance with the concession by the respondent the judgment is reversed. Peyton v. Rowe, 391 U. S. 54.
